arts.ttl: AFC Wimbledon boss Johnnie Jackson: My side proved they are a match for anyone in the division
arts.sum: Doncaster could not turn relentless pressure in the second half into chances and slumped to their first loss in seven games as the Dons went fourth in the League Two standings, ahead of the visitors on goal difference. Johnnie Jackson heaped praise on his players and staff after overseeing Wimbledon’s 1-0 victory over Doncaster from the Plough Lane stands as he served a touchline ban for his actions in their recent game against Newport County.

arts.ttl: Matty Stevens’ 11th goal of the season earns AFC Wimbledon win over Doncaster
